title: 820-3435 Failed Management Engine Presence Test???
message: I have a 820-3435 that powers on, boots to login screen and after I enter password will not boot to the desktop.  The loading bar fills after I enter the password and then it freezes?  I run ASD and it says Chipset (test1)- Management Engine Presence Failed- presence of Management Engine not found???  I have never encountered this error before. Any ideas??

title: 820-3435 Failed Management Engine Presence Test???
message: Someone probably fucked with the SPI ROM to clear the password. Use the attached ROM but edit the serial number. Serial number can be found by searching SSN or ssn in the file.

message:

title: 820-3435 Failed Management Engine Presence Test???
message: Pull off chip and flash my file into it with programmer like TL866 or EZP2010. Edit the serial number with any hex editor of your choice.
